# Documentation & handover governance

**Source of truth:** `AGENTS.md` → **Documentation & Handover Contract**

Context docs (read when changing behavior, phases, or gates):

- `PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md` — status, architecture, remaining work, handover §15
- `docs/diagrams/SYSTEM_DIAGRAMS.md` — Mermaid flows/architecture (mandatory handover artifact)
- `phase-summaries/README.md` — per-phase summary template
- `phase-summaries/phase-{x}.md` — one file per closed/partial phase
- `knowledge/07-testing/loop-engineering/` — Loop Engineering QA scenarios + sanitized readiness reports

## Before finishing work

If you changed runtime code, APIs, phases, gates, tests, or verification status:

1. **Honesty:** separate **code-complete** (pytest green) from **production-verified** (live + owner evidence). Never claim live verification from tests alone.
2. **Phase summary:** create/update `phase-summaries/phase-{x}.md` — สิ่งที่ทำแล้ว, งานคงเหลือ, เกตที่ค้าง, commits (hash **after push**), วันที่.
3. **Overview:** update `PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md` header commit/date; §3 readiness, §11 remaining work, §15 handover when relevant.
4. **Diagrams:** if flows, architecture, agent graph, job kinds, data-source fallback, insight/learning/digest pipelines, or phase readiness changed — update relevant section(s) in `docs/diagrams/SYSTEM_DIAGRAMS.md` in the same change set; note diagram debt if deferred.
5. **README:** sync install/run/env if those paths changed; link to overview for deep context.
6. **Phase doc + gate:** G–K work also updates `knowledge/05-architecture/phases/` and `gates/` per roadmap §4.
7. **Loop Engineering:** if you ran readiness or opened QA defects — write sanitized run-report/readiness under `knowledge/07-testing/loop-engineering/` (QA recommends only; never replaces human gates). Use skill `loop-engineering-qa` when the user asks to test readiness.

## Before phase handover

- [ ] Phase doc DoD + gate (or sign-off) have real evidence
- [ ] Phase summary matches gate/overview (no invented work)
- [ ] PROJECT_OVERVIEW §3/§11/§15 consistent with summaries
- [ ] SYSTEM_DIAGRAMS.md — diagrams match real behavior, or diagram debt noted
- [ ] README run/setup still accurate
- [ ] Loop Engineering readiness linked if relevant (recommend only — not owner sign-off)

When in doubt, update §11 and state what is **not** production-verified.
